<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-10-14T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-10-14T18:00:00-05:00" n="601" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d601">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">701.9111/656: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Moose</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-10-14T18:00:00-05:00">October 14, 1938—6
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>47. Your No. 111, October 12, 4 p.m. The Department assumes that the
                                next step toward the resumption of normal diplomatic relations will
                                be in the form of a proposal by the Iranian Government for <pb facs="0752" n="744" xml:id="pg_744"/> the simultaneous
                                appointment of Ministers. It is further assumed that definitive
                                action in the matter will not be taken until sufficient time has
                                elapsed to permit of the delivery of the Shah’s letter to the
                                President. Please confirm and keep Department currently advised of
                                developments.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>